      • getWeightObject

      • similarity

        double similarity​(java.lang.String field)
        Gets a field's data from the MasterContact and Contact object, and the field's weight. Then calls levenRatio to get our ratio of similarity between the two strings. This then multiplies that ratio by the field's weight.
        Parameters:
        field - Data in a column for a record.
        Returns:
        Weighted level of similarity between the MasterContact and Contact's data.

      • CRD

        boolean CRD()
        Checks if the MasterContact and Contact are a known match.
        Returns:
        True if CRDNumber matches. False if not (or empty).

      • levenRatio

        double levenRatio​(java.lang.String masterData,
                  java.lang.String matchData)
        Calls FuzzyWuzzy's 'ratio' function. This returns us with a simple ratio of similarity between the two Strings.
        Parameters:
        masterData - Data-field from MasterContact object.
        matchData - Data-field from Contact object.
        Returns:
        Ratio of similarity (casted to double).

      • checkCRDNotEmpty

        private boolean checkCRDNotEmpty​(java.lang.String CRDNum)
        Checks if CRDNumber is an empty string.
        Parameters:
        CRDNum - Unique data-field per contact.
        Returns:
        True if not empty. False if empty.

      • handleEmail

        private java.lang.String[] handleEmail​(java.lang.String masterEmail,
                                       java.lang.String matchEmail)
        Attempts to split email addresses at the @ symbol. If the two emails have the same domain (i.e gmail.com), then it we only compare the similarity between the handle (i.e john.doe).
        Parameters:
        masterEmail - MasterContact's email.
        matchEmail - Contact's email.
        Returns:
        Array of strings. This is used in the switch-case in this class's similarity function.
